    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted because inter-laboratory reproducibility was demonstrated and the single loading condition is representative of the intended clinical use. All QoI acceptance criteria are satisfied across three independent FEA platforms. The assessment team concludes that the FEA modeling framework is sufficiently credible for the stated COU. Bench testing evidence is referenced throughout the validation report and supports the overall assessment; the credibility claim statement summarises the conclusion.",
